            <div class="section">
                <h3>Understanding the Impact</h3>
                <p>Sexual violence has profound and lasting effects on a survivor’s physical, emotional, and mental health. These effects can persist for years, influencing relationships, self-esteem, and overall well-being.</p>

            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Physical Health Consequences</h3>
            <p>Survivors of sexual violence may experience chronic pain, gynecological complications, gastrointestinal issues, and an increased risk of sexually transmitted infections (STIs). Additionally, stress-related disorders can weaken the immune system, making survivors more vulnerable to illnesses.</p>
        
               
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Mental and Emotional Health Challenges</h3>
                <p>Many survivors struggle with post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), anxiety, depression, and suicidal thoughts. The psychological scars of sexual violence can lead to difficulty in trusting others and developing healthy relationships.</p>
                
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Impact on Daily Life and Relationships</h3>
                <p>Survivors may face difficulties in personal and professional settings. They might withdraw from social interactions, struggle with intimacy, or experience difficulties in maintaining employment due to trauma-related stress.</p>

                
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <h3>5. Be Honest and Provide Complete Information</h3>
                <p>Medical professionals rely on accurate information to diagnose and suggest treatments. Always be honest and thorough about your medical history, lifestyle, and any symptoms you're experiencing. Even details that seem unrelated—such as stress levels, diet, and sleep patterns—can be important in understanding the root cause of your health concerns.</p>

               
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Coping Strategies and Healing</h3>
                <p>Healing from sexual violence is a complex journey. Seeking professional therapy, joining support groups, and practicing self-care strategies can help survivors regain control over their lives. Encouraging open conversations and creating a supportive environment can aid in the healing process.</p>
               
            </div>
            
            <div class="section">
                <h3>Support and Resources</h3>
                <p>Various organizations provide assistance to survivors, including crisis hotlines, counseling services, and legal advocacy. Accessing these resources can be an essential step toward recovery.</p>

               
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h3>Conclusion</h3>
                <p>Sexual violence can leave lasting physical and emotional scars, but healing is possible with the right support and interventions. Raising awareness and offering compassionate care can help survivors reclaim their lives and well-being.</p>

                
